event_blocks.summary:
{
  "updated_summary": "A woman, dressed in a dark gray sports bra, light gray leggings, white socks, and black over-ear headphones, lies on a black gym mat with a RODE microphone attached to her sports bra, delivering clear, instructional speech about core exercises. She begins by verbally demonstrating bicycle crunches, emphasizing the "opposite hand to knee" motion, then transitions to explaining mountain climbers with a count of "One, two, three" and demonstrating "slower ones." Concluding her instructions, she states, "I will do the whole thing now so you guys can watch it anyway, but I hope I explained that well." As she begins performing the exercises, a rhythmic, synth-heavy background music track becomes audible. She executes bicycle crunches with alternating leg and arm movements, accompanied by the on-screen text 'bicycles 30 secs'. She then performs rapid mountain climbers before lowering to her back for standard crunches, indicated by the on-screen text 'crunches 30 secs'. During her workout, she periodically checks her white smartphone positioned on the mat beside her. In the background, dimly lit treadmills, including a 'SPIRIT' branded one, are visible, with another individual using a treadmill. The sequence ends with her continuing crunches, maintaining consistent form in sync with the music."
}
